The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Visteon forms joint ventures with Taco 

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT 

 Mumbai, June 28: Leading automotive supplier Visteon Corporation has joined hands with Tata Automotive Components (Taco) to set up two 50:50 joint venture companies ? Taco Visteon Automotive Products (TVAP) and Visteon Taco Engineering (VTEC).

 Taco Visteon will be a stand-alone entity separate from Visteon India and will manufacture engine induction systems and lighting systems. Visteon Taco Engineering will initially provide computer-aided designing and other engineering services to Visteons facilities globally. Its key customers are expected to be Visteon US and Visteon Europe. Taco Visteon will also use Visteon Tacos engineering services.

 Both the joint venture companies will be based in Pune.

 Visteon is a leading player in delivering climate, interior and electronics components and systems to automobile manufacturers. The joint ventures are an indication of Indias growing importance to Visteons global and Asia Pacific strategy, the company said in a statement. 

 The company will leverage the strengths of both the partners to bring in new technologies and new opportunities in the countrys growing automotive market, it added. 




